  "text": "In [CITATION_1] , difficulty is not manipulated on the basis of intrinsic stimulus characteristics (as in Experiment 1 of this article) but by making T1 less or more frequent. The authors assume that frequent targets are easy and infrequent targets are hard to perceive. However, the data from Martens, Elmallah, et al. (2006, p. 209) suggests the opposite, that is, lower average accuracy scores for frequent than infrequent targets, although the results are not significant ( p values of approximately .10). Consequently, the relationship between frequency and task difficulty in the AB context is unclear.",
